1
00:00:02,208 --> 00:00:04,083
[metronome clicking]

2
00:00:04,166 --> 00:00:06,166
-<i> Kousei, listen to me.</i>

3
00:00:06,250 --> 00:00:07,541
<i>You're going to study</i>
<i>the sheet music</i>

4
00:00:07,625 --> 00:00:09,791
<i>until you know</i>
<i>every note by heart,</i>

5
00:00:09,875 --> 00:00:11,583
<i>and then you're</i>
<i>going to practice it</i>

6
00:00:11,666 --> 00:00:13,083
<i>until it's flawless.</i>

7
00:00:13,166 --> 00:00:15,291
<i>The piano demands</i>
<i>no less than perfection,</i>

8
00:00:15,375 --> 00:00:18,125
<i>so you're going to be perfect.</i>

9
00:00:18,208 --> 00:00:20,625
<i>You're going to play it</i>
<i>exactly as written,</i>

10
00:00:20,708 --> 00:00:23,666
<i>and once you have,</i>
<i>you'll do it again.</i>

11
00:00:24,791 --> 00:00:26,000
<i>Are you stupid?!</i>

12
00:00:26,083 --> 00:00:27,375
<i>The time signature</i>
<i>is right there!</i>

13
00:00:27,458 --> 00:00:30,833
<i>You're not going to sleep</i>
<i>until you master that passage!</i>

14
00:00:30,916 --> 00:00:33,041
- [metronome stops]
-<i> Now stop being a baby,</i>

15
00:00:33,125 --> 00:00:34,750
<i>and play it again.</i>

16
00:00:36,875 --> 00:00:37,958
-<i> Of course Arima won again.</i>

17
00:00:38,041 --> 00:00:40,958
<i>All his mother does</i>
<i>is make him practice.</i>

18
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:42,750
<i>- Surprised there's not</i>
<i>sheet music on his</i>
<i>glasses.</i>

19
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,833
<i>- He wears them</i>
<i>to cover up the black eyes.</i>

20
00:00:44,916 --> 00:00:48,583
<i>- I heard he practices</i>
<i>seven or eight hours every day.</i>

21
00:00:48,666 --> 00:00:50,250
<i>- When does he get to have fun?</i>

22
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:52,916
<i>- I couldn't live like that.</i>
<i>How does he stand it?</i>

23
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,708
<i>- He's like a robot.</i>

24
00:00:55,791 --> 00:00:57,833
KOUSEI:<i> None of them know</i>
<i>what they're talking</i>
<i>about.</i>

25
00:00:57,916 --> 00:01:01,333
<i>It's me and my Mom</i>
<i>versus everybody else.</i>

26
00:01:04,208 --> 00:01:05,708
["Hikaru Nara" playing]

27
00:01:18,041 --> 00:01:20,916
[singing in Japanese]

28
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:38,333
- Onward, ho! [laughs]

29
00:02:38,416 --> 00:02:40,875
[Kousei screaming]

30
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:44,333
- Have you even
played the song together,

31
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:45,708
or are you winging it?

32
00:02:45,791 --> 00:02:47,333
- We're totally winging it!

33
00:02:47,416 --> 00:02:49,916
But we'll be great,
because we're just that awesome!

34
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,958
- You got
a soccer player up here.

35
00:02:52,041 --> 00:02:54,083
You need time to rehearse,
I'll make it happen.

36
00:02:54,166 --> 00:02:56,250
- Shouldn't you two
be in class right now?

37
00:02:56,333 --> 00:02:57,708
And whose bikes
are these, anyway?

38
00:02:57,791 --> 00:03:00,000
WATARI: Don't sweat
the small stuff. Am I right?

39
00:03:06,125 --> 00:03:06,833
- They barrel
for home plate, and...

40
00:03:06,916 --> 00:03:08,958
safe!

41
00:03:09,041 --> 00:03:10,833
- [yelps]
- Sorry, Kousei!

42
00:03:12,041 --> 00:03:12,833
KAORI: We made it here,
you guys,

43
00:03:12,916 --> 00:03:14,375
- and just in time!
- Go for it!

44
00:03:14,458 --> 00:03:17,625
- You're lifesavers,
both of you!

45
00:03:17,708 --> 00:03:18,958
See you inside!

46
00:03:19,041 --> 00:03:19,958
WATARI: Kousei, your feet!

47
00:03:20,041 --> 00:03:21,333
Sneakers ain't gonna fly!

48
00:03:21,416 --> 00:03:23,791
I thought you music prodigies
knew this junk.

49
00:03:23,875 --> 00:03:25,625
- Tsubaki, Watari,

50
00:03:25,708 --> 00:03:27,875
thank you. I'm ready now.

51
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:29,000
- Hmph.
- [chuckles]

52
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:30,375
- It took you long enough.

53
00:03:30,458 --> 00:03:31,250
- Come on, accompanist. Mush!

54
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:34,000
- What am I, a dog sled?

55
00:03:34,083 --> 00:03:36,000
- Double-time it, Kousei!

56
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:38,041
- So now that we
led the horse to water,

57
00:03:38,125 --> 00:03:39,250
is he gonna drink or what?

58
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,125
- Springtime,
it's right around the corner.

59
00:03:46,208 --> 00:03:48,250
- Huh? You missed
the cherry blossoms?

60
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:50,125
April's almost over.

61
00:03:50,208 --> 00:03:52,875
- Hmm. I know.

62
00:03:52,958 --> 00:03:54,083
But still...

63
00:03:56,041 --> 00:03:57,375
it's almost here.

64
00:04:08,625 --> 00:04:11,875
- Next, contestant 12.
Nashida, you're up.

65
00:04:11,958 --> 00:04:15,458
- All right! Now go out there,
and show 'em perfection.

66
00:04:15,541 --> 00:04:17,083
- Uh, yeah!
I'll do my very best, ma'am!

67
00:04:17,166 --> 00:04:19,500
-<i> Jeez.</i>
<i>This how kids get ulcers.</i>

68
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,416
-<i> Clearly I've lost my mind.</i>

69
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:25,041
<i>I should have been running</i>
<i>this piece night and day,</i>

70
00:04:25,125 --> 00:04:26,958
<i>drilling it into my</i>
<i>muscle memory again and again</i>

71
00:04:27,041 --> 00:04:30,125
<i>'til the sheet music</i>
<i>was just an afterthought.</i>

72
00:04:30,208 --> 00:04:32,000
- [mechanical whirring]
-<i> But now it's practically</i>

73
00:04:32,083 --> 00:04:35,875
<i>going to be a cold read.</i>
<i>No problem, right?</i>

74
00:04:35,958 --> 00:04:39,333
<i>I mean, it's not like</i>
<i>she plays like a crazy person.</i>

75
00:04:39,416 --> 00:04:41,958
- So what's the plan?

76
00:04:42,041 --> 00:04:44,958
Start out andante
and then hit the gas?

77
00:04:45,041 --> 00:04:46,708
-<i> Why did I give in?</i>

78
00:04:46,791 --> 00:04:48,041
<i>Our playing this piece,</i>

79
00:04:48,125 --> 00:04:50,083
<i>it's a disaster</i>
<i>waiting to happen.</i>

80
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:52,000
- So what do you think
of the dress?

81
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,458
First time wearing it.

82
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:55,000
<i>- I have to back out</i>
<i>of the competition.</i>

83
00:04:55,083 --> 00:04:56,916
<i>I-It's the right thing to do.</i>

84
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:59,041
<i>We're gonna make fools</i>
<i>of ourselves.</i>

85
00:04:59,125 --> 00:05:00,125
- Snap out of it.

86
00:05:01,083 --> 00:05:01,416
[grunts]

87
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,375
[all gasp]

88
00:05:05,083 --> 00:05:05,500
- Huh?

89
00:05:05,583 --> 00:05:07,166
- [groaning]

90
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:08,208
[all gasp]

91
00:05:08,291 --> 00:05:09,500
ALL: What?!

92
00:05:09,583 --> 00:05:12,541
- So, Friend A, you feel better?

93
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:15,041
- I need my brain
to work right now! [gasps]

94
00:05:15,125 --> 00:05:17,708
- Just shut up, and look at me,

95
00:05:17,791 --> 00:05:19,500
not at the music
or at the floor.

96
00:05:19,583 --> 00:05:22,666
You've always
got your head down.

97
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:25,125
You're stuck in that score
like it's quicksand.

98
00:05:25,208 --> 00:05:26,833
- [gasps]

99
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:28,000
- Don't worry.

100
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:29,500
I know you can do it.

101
00:05:29,583 --> 00:05:31,916
Saint-Saens was
your lunch soundtrack,

102
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,375
and the score itself,
we plastered your world with it.

103
00:05:35,458 --> 00:05:38,875
The song is in you.

104
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:42,041
[sighs]

105
00:05:42,875 --> 00:05:45,416
"Go on a journey,
you crazy kids."

106
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:47,708
That's what Mozart's saying.

107
00:05:47,791 --> 00:05:49,875
"Travelers need feel no shame,"

108
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:52,041
so whatever we do,
we're fine out there.

109
00:05:52,125 --> 00:05:53,541
We're together.

110
00:05:53,625 --> 00:05:54,875
- [sighs]

111
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:58,750
- Next is 14, Kaori Miyazono.

112
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:00,375
It's time to take the stage.

113
00:06:00,458 --> 00:06:00,875
- [grunts]

114
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:07,291
- That's our cue.

115
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:16,833
<i>- Listen, Kousei.</i>

116
00:06:16,916 --> 00:06:18,916
<i>Only play what's on the page.</i>

117
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,583
<i>Who are you</i>
<i>to second-guess the greats?</i>

118
00:06:20,666 --> 00:06:24,166
KOUSEI:<i> Raging one second</i>

119
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:26,125
<i>and still the next.</i>

120
00:06:26,208 --> 00:06:30,416
<i>Every moment I spend with her</i>
<i>is like a roller coaster.</i>

121
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,875
<i>She is the journey</i>

122
00:06:32,958 --> 00:06:35,208
<i>with no clear destination</i>
<i>in sight.</i>

123
00:06:36,625 --> 00:06:39,208
It's like you're freedom itself.

124
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:43,125
- No, I'm not.

125
00:06:43,208 --> 00:06:45,666
Freedom is
what we find out there.

126
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:59,458
KOUSEI:<i> This silence</i>
<i>belongs to us,</i>

127
00:06:59,541 --> 00:07:01,500
<i>and every single person</i>
<i>out there</i>

128
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:04,458
<i>is waiting for us</i>
<i>to fill it with something.</i>

129
00:07:09,125 --> 00:07:11,458
- Come on. It's time to go.

130
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:14,458
We don't want
to keep Saint-Saens waiting.

131
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,583
[footsteps echoing]

132
00:07:22,583 --> 00:07:24,291
- [gasps]
- It's them.

133
00:07:24,375 --> 00:07:25,458
- She looks amazing!

134
00:07:25,541 --> 00:07:26,291
[audience murmuring]

135
00:07:26,375 --> 00:07:28,250
- The accompanist
is a kid, too.

136
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:30,958
- You're right.
- Hang on a sec. Isn't that...

137
00:07:31,041 --> 00:07:32,083
[applause]

138
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:38,041
<i>- Kaori Miyazono.</i>
<i>We meet again.</i>

139
00:07:38,125 --> 00:07:41,458
<i>Eh? She's got</i>
<i>a different accompanist,</i>

140
00:07:41,541 --> 00:07:43,000
<i>and he's just a kid, too.</i>

141
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:44,666
KAORI: What are you
doing back there?

142
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:46,500
- I'm having trouble
adjusting the bench.

143
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:47,958
- Get the lead out, tree sloth.

144
00:07:48,041 --> 00:07:49,583
I want to play sometime today.

145
00:07:49,666 --> 00:07:52,166
JUDGE:<i> Where do I</i>
<i>know that face from?</i>

146
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:54,333
- It's Arima, the pianist.

147
00:07:54,416 --> 00:07:55,125
- That Arima?

148
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:57,291
- My word. Who'd have thought

149
00:07:57,375 --> 00:07:58,500
that the Arima boy
would make an appearance?

150
00:07:58,583 --> 00:07:59,583
-<i> That's him.</i>

151
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:02,041
<i>He's a teenager now,</i>

152
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:04,083
<i>but there's</i>
<i>no mistaking that face.</i>

153
00:08:04,166 --> 00:08:05,416
- Sorry. Sorry.
- JUDGE:<i> Kousei Arima.</i>

154
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:07,000
- Just gotta lower it
a bit more.

155
00:08:07,083 --> 00:08:08,666
-<i> Why is he accompanying her?</i>

156
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:10,500
<i>Are they school friends</i>
<i>or something?</i>

157
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:11,666
- [sighs]

158
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:13,125
That'll do nicely.

159
00:08:13,208 --> 00:08:14,125
- Princess.

160
00:08:14,208 --> 00:08:15,625
-<i> Huh.</i>

161
00:08:15,708 --> 00:08:17,125
<i>The robot and the free spirit.</i>

162
00:08:17,208 --> 00:08:20,333
<i>They're an odd couple.</i>
<i>I'll give 'em that.</i>

163
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:23,375
<i>What sort of song</i>
<i>will you bring to life?</i>

164
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:28,166
- [breathes deeply]

165
00:08:29,541 --> 00:08:30,708
<i>Elohim, Essaim. Elohim, Essaim.</i>

166
00:08:30,791 --> 00:08:33,625
Most humbly, I implore you.

167
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:38,625
- [grunts]

168
00:08:38,708 --> 00:08:41,166
- [gasps] It probably
wouldn't kill you to smile.

169
00:08:47,375 --> 00:08:48,541
-<i> Our piece was dedicated</i>

170
00:08:48,625 --> 00:08:51,875
<i>to the virtuoso violist,</i>
<i>Sarasate,</i>

171
00:08:51,958 --> 00:08:56,000
<i>Saint-Saens' "Introduction</i>
<i>and Rondo Capriccioso."</i>

172
00:08:59,291 --> 00:09:02,000
[playing "Introduction
and Rondo Capriccioso"]

173
00:09:11,125 --> 00:09:13,250
<i>All right, so far, so good.</i>

174
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:14,958
<i>I can hear the notes.</i>

175
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:16,708
<i>This song was a wise choice.</i>

176
00:09:26,541 --> 00:09:28,625
<i>There are some parts</i>
<i>where I could go off-key,</i>

177
00:09:28,708 --> 00:09:33,125
<i>but if I heed the violin</i>
<i>and keep an eye on the score,</i>

178
00:09:33,208 --> 00:09:35,208
<i>it shouldn't pose</i>
<i>any sort of challenge.</i>

179
00:09:35,666 --> 00:09:37,875
- [sighs]

180
00:09:37,958 --> 00:09:41,041
<i>Kousei's finally</i>
<i>playing the piano again.</i>

181
00:09:41,125 --> 00:09:43,750
-<i> What's your game, Miyazono?</i>

182
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:47,416
<i>You were a firebrand before,</i>
<i>and now this.</i>

183
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:49,625
<i>Deferring to your accompanist,</i>
<i>maybe?</i>

184
00:09:50,541 --> 00:09:52,083
- [gasps]

185
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:02,458
-<i> Here we go. Off to the races.</i>

186
00:10:17,541 --> 00:10:20,208
- No way.

187
00:10:35,541 --> 00:10:37,083
- [gasps]

188
00:10:54,750 --> 00:10:56,291
<i>All the notes...</i>

189
00:10:57,416 --> 00:10:58,583
<i>they're vanishing.</i>

190
00:11:02,583 --> 00:11:04,166
[drip echoes]

191
00:11:04,250 --> 00:11:04,750
[music distorts]

192
00:11:04,833 --> 00:11:07,541
[bubbles popping]

193
00:11:09,625 --> 00:11:10,541
<i>The sound of the piano,</i>

194
00:11:10,625 --> 00:11:12,875
<i>I can't hear it.</i>

195
00:11:12,958 --> 00:11:14,958
[thumping]

196
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,708
[gasps]

197
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:24,166
- [gasps]

198
00:11:28,375 --> 00:11:28,958
-<i> Huh? What happened?</i>

199
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:31,750
- Whoa. He's kinda off.

200
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,708
-<i> They're not maintaining tempo.</i>

201
00:11:33,791 --> 00:11:35,416
- Kousei, no.

202
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:37,750
-<i> Somewhere inside this robot,</i>

203
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:40,625
<i>who crushed his opponents</i>
<i>with unblinking precision,</i>

204
00:11:40,708 --> 00:11:42,500
<i>a gear has slipped.</i>

205
00:11:43,791 --> 00:11:44,750
- [gasps]

206
00:11:44,833 --> 00:11:47,666
[keys thumping]

207
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:49,750
<i>I'm at the bottom</i>
<i>of a sunless sea,</i>

208
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:50,791
<i>deaf and cold.</i>

209
00:11:50,875 --> 00:11:54,083
<i>There's no one else,</i>

210
00:11:54,166 --> 00:11:57,750
<i>just me alone in the dark,</i>

211
00:11:57,833 --> 00:12:00,250
<i>and now I'm sinking</i>
<i>even deeper.</i>

212
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:01,708
<i>They're never going to find me.</i>

213
00:12:01,791 --> 00:12:03,875
[violin continues]

214
00:12:06,708 --> 00:12:08,333
[piano resumes]

215
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:13,500
- He started out okay enough,

216
00:12:13,583 --> 00:12:15,708
but now he's
just pounding the keys.

217
00:12:15,791 --> 00:12:17,500
- Where'd they find this kid?

218
00:12:17,583 --> 00:12:19,208
- Too bad for his partner, huh?

219
00:12:19,291 --> 00:12:21,041
-<i> He's no accompanist,</i>

220
00:12:21,125 --> 00:12:22,000
<i>but at least</i>
<i>he was holding his own.</i>

221
00:12:22,083 --> 00:12:24,750
<i>What just happened, Arima?</i>

222
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:28,208
<i>Don't you see you're strangling</i>
<i>her performance to death?</i>

223
00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:31,000
[music distorts]

224
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:32,958
- [keys thumping]
-<i> No. No, damn it.</i>

225
00:12:33,041 --> 00:12:36,458
<i>I'm pounding the keys</i>
<i>so hard, so why?!</i>

226
00:12:36,541 --> 00:12:39,458
<i>Why is my playing</i>
<i>the only thing I can't hear?!</i>

227
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:43,583
[violin continues]

228
00:12:44,708 --> 00:12:46,958
[notes play]

229
00:12:47,041 --> 00:12:49,458
- [gasps]
- [audience gasps]

230
00:12:49,541 --> 00:12:50,416
[murmuring]

231
00:12:51,916 --> 00:12:54,791
[violin continues]

232
00:12:57,375 --> 00:12:59,416
- [gasps]

233
00:12:59,875 --> 00:13:01,750
- [sighs]

234
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:04,291
-<i> Drastic, but clever.</i>

235
00:13:04,375 --> 00:13:05,041
<i>She's sure</i>
<i>to lose points for it,</i>

236
00:13:05,125 --> 00:13:07,458
<i>but fewer than she'd lose</i>

237
00:13:07,541 --> 00:13:09,875
<i>if he kept dragging down</i>
<i>her performance like that.</i>

238
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:16,166
- Way to drop the ball,
kid.
- Don't ruin it for her.

239
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:17,958
- What made him think
he could do this?

240
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,750
-<i> I'm sorry.</i>

241
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:22,333
<i>If I kept playing like this...</i>

242
00:13:23,708 --> 00:13:25,333
<i>like a novice,</i>

243
00:13:25,416 --> 00:13:27,333
<i>it'd just make things worse.</i>

244
00:13:27,416 --> 00:13:28,750
[violin continues]

245
00:13:34,958 --> 00:13:36,833
- [bow taps]
- [violin stops]

246
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:37,458
[gasps]

247
00:13:39,958 --> 00:13:40,833
[gasps]

248
00:13:40,916 --> 00:13:43,708
[audience murmuring]

249
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:48,958
[both gasp]

250
00:13:51,875 --> 00:13:54,500
- What's going on? She was
doing so well by herself.

251
00:13:54,583 --> 00:13:56,083
Why'd she stop?

252
00:14:04,416 --> 00:14:06,375
[audience murmuring]

253
00:14:06,458 --> 00:14:07,500
- [panting]

254
00:14:13,791 --> 00:14:15,291
- Are they disqualified?

255
00:14:15,375 --> 00:14:16,875
- Not technically,
but they are out.

256
00:14:16,958 --> 00:14:18,958
- The unmitigated nerve.

257
00:14:19,041 --> 00:14:21,041
- [sighs]

258
00:14:21,125 --> 00:14:21,750
So much for that.

259
00:14:21,833 --> 00:14:24,416
- So why did she stop?

260
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:25,791
- That accompanist
really killed her chances,

261
00:14:25,875 --> 00:14:28,708
and she was so cool.

262
00:14:31,916 --> 00:14:33,750
KAORI:<i> Don't worry.</i>

263
00:14:33,833 --> 00:14:36,000
<i>I know you can do it.</i>

264
00:14:37,583 --> 00:14:40,750
<i>I give the accompanist job</i>
<i>to Friend A.</i>

265
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,916
<i>You have to keep playing.</i>

266
00:14:46,375 --> 00:14:48,416
<i>And I want you with me anyway.</i>

267
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,541
<i>I'll give it</i>
<i>everything I've got.</i>

268
00:14:52,958 --> 00:14:54,875
<i>And the people who hear it,</i>

269
00:14:54,958 --> 00:14:56,541
<i>they'll never forget me.</i>

270
00:14:58,291 --> 00:15:00,750
<i>I was put on this Earth</i>
<i>to make music.</i>

271
00:15:04,083 --> 00:15:05,416
Again?

272
00:15:07,458 --> 00:15:08,791
- [grunts]

273
00:15:08,875 --> 00:15:10,583
-<i> It's dark,</i>

274
00:15:10,666 --> 00:15:12,875
<i>and we can't see</i>
<i>where the road leads,</i>

275
00:15:12,958 --> 00:15:15,416
<i>but trust in me,</i>
<i>and take another step.</i>

276
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:19,125
<i>The stars will light our path,</i>
<i>however faintly.</i>

277
00:15:19,208 --> 00:15:20,541
<i>I know they will.</i>

278
00:15:28,083 --> 00:15:29,291
<i>Come on.</i>

279
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:30,958
<i>Our journey awaits.</i>

280
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,416
[playing "Introduction
and Rondo Capriccioso"]

281
00:15:50,375 --> 00:15:52,625
- Can they just start up again?

282
00:15:52,708 --> 00:15:55,333
- So long as they don't
run over, they can do whatever,

283
00:15:55,416 --> 00:15:56,875
but nothing after she stopped
will count.

284
00:15:56,958 --> 00:15:58,833
- [gasps]

285
00:15:58,916 --> 00:15:59,916
- No matter what she does,

286
00:16:00,041 --> 00:16:02,791
she's out of the running.

287
00:16:02,875 --> 00:16:07,041
- So then she's just playing
to play right now?

288
00:16:07,125 --> 00:16:08,916
- Start hitting the keys,
you idiot.

289
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,833
If you leave her hanging,
I'm so kicking your ass.

290
00:16:10,916 --> 00:16:13,208
-<i> Please.</i>

291
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:18,750
KOUSEI:<i> I'm still</i>
<i>looking for any excuse,</i>

292
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:22,166
<i>but this time,</i>
<i>it's for a reason to say yes.</i>

293
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:23,791
[violin continues]

294
00:16:23,875 --> 00:16:25,583
-<i> The song is in you.</i>

295
00:16:27,250 --> 00:16:30,291
KOUSEI:<i> There was</i>
<i>such resolve in your eyes.</i>

296
00:16:30,375 --> 00:16:33,875
<i>I-I could never</i>
<i>hope to match it.</i>

297
00:16:35,083 --> 00:16:36,291
-<i> You'll have me this time.</i>

298
00:16:36,375 --> 00:16:39,875
<i>Just shut up, and look at me,</i>
<i>not at the music.</i>

299
00:16:39,958 --> 00:16:40,500
- [gasps]

300
00:16:42,375 --> 00:16:44,083
-<i> Look at me.</i>

301
00:16:47,458 --> 00:16:49,208
KOUSEI:<i> Brace yourself, Kousei.</i>

302
00:16:49,291 --> 00:16:51,000
[playing "Introduction
and Rondo Capriccioso"]

303
00:16:51,083 --> 00:16:52,875
- Right on!
- Now we're talking!

304
00:16:52,958 --> 00:16:54,625
- He started up.

305
00:16:54,708 --> 00:16:57,875
-<i> Gutsy, but they're just</i>
<i>as out of sync as before.</i>

306
00:16:57,958 --> 00:17:00,041
<i>It's your move, Arima.</i>

307
00:17:00,125 --> 00:17:02,875
KOUSEI:<i> Focus. Focus.</i>

308
00:17:02,958 --> 00:17:03,458
Focus!

309
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,750
<i>The score is blank,</i>

310
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:07,500
<i>and the piano has gone mute.</i>

311
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:10,791
<i>For a whole week,</i>

312
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:13,791
<i>the sheet music</i>
<i>dogged my every step.</i>

313
00:17:13,875 --> 00:17:16,791
<i>It's all I heard</i>
<i>during my lunches.</i>

314
00:17:16,875 --> 00:17:19,250
<i>Whatever's inside of me,</i>
<i>draw it out.</i>

315
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:19,875
[distorted notes playing]

316
00:17:19,958 --> 00:17:23,375
<i>Focus. Focus.</i>

317
00:17:23,458 --> 00:17:26,458
<i>Focus! Come on!</i>

318
00:17:26,541 --> 00:17:28,375
SAKI:<i> Listen, Kousei.</i>

319
00:17:29,625 --> 00:17:32,625
<i>You don't have to hit</i>
<i>the keys so hard, honey.</i>

320
00:17:32,708 --> 00:17:34,875
<i>Put yourself in its place.</i>

321
00:17:34,958 --> 00:17:37,625
<i>If you tickle it gently,</i>
<i>it will laugh.</i>

322
00:17:37,708 --> 00:17:40,166
<i>Hitting it just makes it mad.</i>

323
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:42,625
<i>Touch it like you're petting</i>
<i>a little kitten.</i>

324
00:17:42,708 --> 00:17:44,708
<i>Now try it again.</i>

325
00:17:46,125 --> 00:17:51,125
<i>♪ Twinkle, twinkle,</i>
<i>little star ♪</i>

326
00:17:51,208 --> 00:17:56,666
<i>♪ How I wonder what you are ♪</i>

327
00:17:56,750 --> 00:18:00,250
<i>♪ Up above the world so high ♪</i>

328
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:06,791
<i>♪ Like a diamond in the sky ♪</i>

329
00:18:06,875 --> 00:18:12,083
<i>♪ Twinkle, twinkle,</i>
<i>little star ♪</i>

330
00:18:12,166 --> 00:18:17,750
<i>♪ How I wonder what you are ♪</i>

331
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,083
[violin playing]

332
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:23,125
- [piano resumes]
- [gasps]

333
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:27,916
KOUSEI:<i> If you</i>
<i>can't hear the sound,</i>

334
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:28,750
<i>then imagine it.</i>

335
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:31,666
<i>Play it with your whole body.</i>

336
00:18:31,750 --> 00:18:33,958
<i>Take everything</i>
<i>that Mom left me,</i>

337
00:18:34,041 --> 00:18:35,333
<i>and draw it out!</i>

338
00:18:52,208 --> 00:18:54,000
-<i> Don't you get cocky,</i>
<i>Friend A.</i>

339
00:18:55,791 --> 00:18:58,791
<i>You're not stealing</i>
<i>my thunder that easily.</i>

340
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:06,958
-<i> No way.</i>

341
00:19:07,041 --> 00:19:08,333
- Kaori! Kousei!

342
00:19:08,416 --> 00:19:09,000
- Shush! Shh!
- You two are amazing!

343
00:19:09,083 --> 00:19:12,958
- She's beautiful.

344
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:14,500
-<i> This is outrageous.</i>

345
00:19:14,583 --> 00:19:16,125
<i>They're both out of control.</i>

346
00:19:16,208 --> 00:19:18,000
<i>It's like I'm watching</i>
<i>a fistfight.</i>

347
00:19:18,083 --> 00:19:20,666
<i>With every punch they throw,</i>

348
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:23,166
<i>the audience</i>
<i>hungers for more of it.</i>

349
00:19:43,458 --> 00:19:45,375
<i>He's boxing at a disadvantage.</i>

350
00:19:45,458 --> 00:19:46,875
<i>This isn't his weight class.</i>

351
00:19:46,958 --> 00:19:50,458
<i>He's a soloist, like her.</i>

352
00:19:50,541 --> 00:19:51,625
-<i> She moves me forward</i>

353
00:19:51,708 --> 00:19:55,458
<i>relentlessly,</i>
<i>like a heartbeat.</i>

354
00:19:56,875 --> 00:19:58,791
<i>The music is everywhere.</i>

355
00:19:59,916 --> 00:20:01,541
<i>You're with me!</i>

356
00:20:13,166 --> 00:20:15,958
[piece ends]

357
00:20:16,041 --> 00:20:18,291
[wind blowing]

358
00:20:21,416 --> 00:20:25,375
<i>April, it's almost over.</i>

359
00:20:29,958 --> 00:20:31,458
[audience cheering]

360
00:20:31,541 --> 00:20:32,833
- Bravo!

361
00:20:32,916 --> 00:20:33,416
- You kids are unbelievable!

362
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:35,125
- That was awesome!

363
00:20:35,208 --> 00:20:36,750
- Encore! Encore!

364
00:20:37,666 --> 00:20:40,875
- This is not
some rock concert!

365
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:45,250
KOUSEI:<i> The cool, dry air.</i>

366
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:47,875
<i>The scent of dust.</i>

367
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,125
<i>My journey...</i>

368
00:20:52,208 --> 00:20:53,291
<i>has begun.</i>

369
00:20:53,375 --> 00:20:55,416
[cheering continues]

370
00:21:05,208 --> 00:21:06,083
[thump]

371
00:21:06,166 --> 00:21:09,500
[thump echoing]

372
00:21:20,541 --> 00:21:22,541
["Kirameki" playing]

373
00:21:23,375 --> 00:21:25,541
[singing in Japanese]

